               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1872" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1872" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1872" type="surname" value="RYDER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1872" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD RYDER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Fore-street, Lambeth—the prisoner was in my service. On the 25th of July, I gave him 1152 pipes to take to Mr. Hardy, in Wellington-square—he ought to have come back the same evening, and brought 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., or the pipes; he did not return—I never saw the pipes nor him, till I found him in the Swan and Horse-shoe, enlisted for a soldier.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You asked him what he had done with the pipes, and he gave you a saucy answer? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I do not know that I have ever sent him round with pipes to sell where he could—I had paid him his wages on the Saturday night before he went away, all but 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he worked with me on the Monday, and on Tuesday he left—he boarded with me—I believe I owe his mother half-a-crown.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184308210247"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1873" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1873" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1873" type="surname" value="HARDY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1873" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HARDY</persName>
                  </hi>. I did not receive these pipes on the 25th of July—I did not see the prisoner on that day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Were you at home all day? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—it was im<lb></lb>possible for eight gross of pipes to come without my knowing it.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
